title: For Sale:  "ASSAULT" RIFLES AND WEAPONS
postcontent:
ARMSLIST and all other gun marketplaces are community run for the most part. As a gun community we need to come together to rid ourselves of one of the deadliest sins - greed. We are all tired of seeing $500 AK-47s listed at $2000, and $800 fully upgraded AR-15s posted for $4500. Guess what? As gun buyers and members on this and other forums, we are just as responsible for the state of our society as the price gougers, hoarders and ban pushing politicians. We need to come together and do two things: (1) STOP BUYING AT THESE RIDICULOUS PRICES and (2) click on the ad, go to "Flag" at the top, and press "overpriced." This whole process takes 1.3968 seconds.

These price criminals only have business if someone is ignorant enough to buy and if they spread their advertisement. NOTE TO GUN COMMUNITY: Guns aren't going anywhere. Ammo isn't going anywhere. Magazines are the biggest threat of changing but let's face it, do we really need 100 round drums or is that more of a want? Every time you skip over a $10,000 ad for a $3000 purchased SCAR 17, you have just became part of the problem. Send them a hate email showing the prices before hoarding and then promptly flag their ad so we can get prices back under the 1000s where they all belong. For the uninformed or misinformed audience, I have put together a short list of reasonable prices for standard guns. What I am asking is that everyone read this post and then immediately copy and paste it to another state's listing in the US. Add your own two cents in if you'd like or if I got anything wrong. The regularity will only return if we make it.

At the Ohio Deer and Turkey Expo this weekend, several booths had so called 'P-Mags' for sale.  The only difference is that at the expo, they were priced at $15 MAYBE $20, whereas on Armslist, you are told that they are vanishing into thin air and are worth their weight in gold.  20 and 30 round mags are readily available and easy to find.  

AR-15: $600-$1300 depending on brand and usage (shots fired, wear, etc..)
 AK-47: $400-$900
 SKS:$300-$500
 SCAR 16/17: $2000/$2800
 AR-10: $1000-1500
 Glock: $400-600
 10/22: $229

DO NOT PAY THE OBSCENE PRICES HOARDERS AND FEARMONGERS WANT YOU TO.
